◆ rlOsiSpawn

rlInt32_t(* rlOsiMsgQCbs_t::rlOsiSpawn)(RL_P_OSI_SPAWN_ENTRY pEntry, void *pValue, rlUInt32_t flags)

Calls a function in a different context.

Parameters
[in]pEntry- Pointer to Entry Function
[in]pValue- Pointer to data passed to function
[in]flags- Flag to indicate preference
Returns
rlInt32_t Success - 0, Failure - Error code

Calls a function in a different context. mmWaveLink Driver Interrupt handler function invokes this interface to switch context so that Interrupt Service Routine is executed immediately. mmWaveLink uses this callback function to invoke 'rlDriverMsgReadSpawnCtx' funtion to read the async-event message in different interrupt context. Host should able to handle the error code generated by 'rlDriverMsgReadSpawnCtx' spawned function.
